<item>
            <title>[IO-853] BoundedInputStream.reset() not updating count</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-853</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-io/commit/99702ec5ce4c25a909299c4f4a8be616d8ce04dc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-io/commit/99702ec5ce4c25a909299c4f4a8be616d8ce04dc&lt;/a&gt; BoundedInputStream was modified to use a CountingInputStream, and reset() no longer set the count to the mark, because count was retrieved from the other stream.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-io/commit/812d8a4b53d9758b4f081d9b98a70ea9ef131a0e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-io/commit/812d8a4b53d9758b4f081d9b98a70ea9ef131a0e&lt;/a&gt; the count field was added back in but reset() was not fixed to update the value of count when called.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes a regression, found when attempting to upgrade commons-compress.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
